Helpfully, besides a common name label, Statistical Areas are also indexed by a structured code representing their classification hierarchy. For example, SA1 regions are denoted by an 11 digit code which can be decomposed into the higher level area codes in which the region sits. @fig-FootscraySA1Code demonstrates this for the Footscray SA1 region considered above.

